# ThreadSanitizer suppressions for the lock-free token-bucket stress
# (test-rate-stress.c). ONE entry, tightly scoped + documented.
#
# ngx_http_heavybag_rate_check uses the nginx lock-free idiom: an OPTIMISTIC
# PLAIN read of the packed slot word (old = s->state; k = cand->key) followed
# by a __sync compare-and-swap that re-validates `old`. On x86 (and every
# platform nginx targets) this is correct -- a stale read just loses the CAS
# and retries -- but the plain read is, strictly, a C11 data race against the
# atomic write, so TSan reports it. ngx_atomic_t IS that relaxed-read /
# cmp_set-write word; this is identical to nginx core's own atomics and is the
# DELIBERATE design, not a bug.
#
# Scoping the suppression to this ONE function means TSan still flags any
# UNINTENDED race anywhere else (the shm header, the slot-array indexing, the
# per-thread result counters, the clock global) and still aborts on a crash --
# which is what the stress run actually validates, alongside outcome
# conservation and slot integrity.
race:ngx_http_heavybag_rate_check
